cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on resource allocation and task scheduling in a cloud computing environment, which falls under the scope of distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the optimization of resource allocation and task scheduling, which is relevant to computational science and engineering. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an algorithm to improve the performance of cloud scheduling, which can be seen as a control problem in a system. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Cloud computing heavily relies on networking and internet architecture, and the paper may discuss the impact of these factors on resource allocation and task scheduling. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may discuss the software engineering aspects of implementing the proposed algorithm in a cloud computing environment.
